                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“I have been crucified with Christ; it is no longer I who live, but Christ lives in me; and the life which I now live in the flesh I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave Himself for me.”
                                                                            <b>Galatians 2:20 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“For in it the righteousness of God is revealed from faith to faith; as it is written, “The just shall live by faith.””
                                                                            <b>Romans 1:17 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“above all, taking the shield of faith with which you will be able to quench all the fiery darts of the wicked one.  And take the helmet of salvation and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God.” <b>Ephesians 6:16-17 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">How do we fight the daily battle, more so the blatant attacks that want to take us down to discouragement and despair and sin.  There is one very important fact we must all remember.  We gave our lives to Jesus Christ.  There is nothing that can happen to us that He doesn’t know about.  Everything is filtered through His hand.  He has made every provision for us to be empowered and ready for the battle.  We can’t loose with Him.  If God is for us, who can be against us?”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">As we continue adding pieces of armor we must look at key words in the text.  Having and taking.  “Having” gird ourselves with truth, “having” put on righteousness, “having” shod our feet with the Gospel.  We turn to “above all” which means “also”, “taking” the shield of faith, “take” the helmet of salvation, the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">The first three pieces of armor we are to wear continually.  We are committed to the truth, we are always walking in right standing with God and we stand in total confidence of the Gospel.  These three pieces are engrained.  The following three are added resources and assurance of our victory.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Today we apply the shield of faith.  What is faith?  Simply put it is the complete confidence and trust in God that He is who He says He is and has done what He said He would do!
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">By faith we can understand how faith works as in <b>Hebrews 11:1</b>, “it is the substance of things hoped for, and the evidence of things not seen.  Our assurance in God rests on the promises of God.  He is who He says He is. We trust Him.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Our faith in Him quenches all the fiery darts that come our way.  Satan uses the same tactics he used in the Garden of Eden to tempt Eve.  The lust of the flesh, the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life.  Just as with Eve Satan does not want us to believe God and wants us to doubt Him.  Ungodly temptations, and they come in all shapes and sizes, and are personal.  An ungodly temptation to one may not be a temptation to another.  God has inbred us with the knowledge of what is right and what is wrong.  When temptation arises the Holy Spirit will always quicken us to it and the choice is ours.  This is when we pick up our shield of faith.  “Yet we are more than conquerors through Him who loves us.” <b>Romans 8:37</b>.  May the battle be won in your life!
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Father we praise Your mighty name and want to be committed, walking in righteousness, in the full confidence of the Gospel of Jesus Christ.  May our inner conscience that You have placed within us be active making us aware of the enemies tactics and or our own fleshy desires we may have allowed access to us.  May we pick up our shield of faith and as Your word says those fiery darts will be quenched.  We ask believing in Jesus name.  Amen!
                                                                        </p>
